    <stitle>VT-365 Diesel Engine Diagnostics (2002) - PERFORMANCE DIAGNOSTICS - Test Procedures - Air Management
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="3">
        <title>Air Management</title>
        <figure id="f2400674" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figD31/D3154.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
        </figure>
        <para>
            <emph type="bold">Purpose</emph>
        </para>
        <para>To determine if intake, exhaust, EVRT&#8482;, and EGR systems are working correctly</para>
        <para>
            <emph type="bold">Tools</emph>
            <emph type="bold"></emph>
        </para>
        <randlist type="bullet">
            <item>
                <para>Electronic Service Tool (EST) with Master Diagnostics software</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>International&#174; EZ-Tech Interface Cable</para>
            </item>
        </randlist>
        <specpara>
            <warning>
                <para>To avoid serious personal injury, possible death, or damage to the engine or vehicle, read all
                    safety instructions in the foreword of this manual. Follow all warnings, cautions, and notes.
                </para>
            </warning>
        </specpara>
        <para>
            <emph type="bold">Procedure</emph>
        </para>
        <specpara>
            <warning>
                <para>To prevent serious personal injury, possible death, or damage to the engine or vehicle - comply
                    with the following:
                </para>
                <para>When running the engine in the service bay, make sure the parking brake is set, the transmission
                    is in neutral, and the wheels are blocked.
                </para>
            </warning>
        </specpara>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Test 12 (Key On Engine Running) must have been done before doing this test.</para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <figure id="f2400675" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figD31/D31197.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>KOER Air Management.ssn</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Open KOER Air Management.ssn to monitor engine operation.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f27400676" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figD31/D31201.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="yes"/>
            <caption>Air Management Test</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Select Diagnostics from menu bar.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Select Key On Engine Running Tests from the drop down menu.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Select Air Management Test and click Run to start the test.</para>
            <para>The ECM will start the Air Management Test and command the engine to accelerate to a predetermined
                engine rpm. The ECM will monitor the effects of the EVRT&#8482; and EGR valve movement using the EBP
                sensor.
            </para>
            <randlist type="bullet">
                <item>
                    <para>If a problem is detected the ECM will cancel the test, set a DTC, and restore normal engine
                        operation.
                    </para>
                </item>
            </randlist>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Record all DTCs on Performance Diagnostics form.</para>
            <para>See Appendix B in this manual for DTCs.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Correct problems causing active DTCs.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Clear DTCs.</para>
        </step1>
        <para>
            <emph type="bold">Possible Causes</emph>
        </para>
        <randlist type="bullet">
            <item>
                <para>Exhaust leaks</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Intake leaks</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Plugged EBP tube assembly</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Defective EGR valve</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Biased MAP or EBP sensor</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Defective EVRT&#8482; control valve</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Defective turbocharger</para>
            </item>
        </randlist>
    </svcproc>
